JOHANNESBURG - The family of the soon-to-be queen of AmaZulu, Ntokozo Mayisela, says she is ready for the challenge. His Majesty King Misuzulu kaZwelithini sent a delegation from the royal house to negotiate lobola. READ: Royal lobola negotiations begin Part of the lobola for 37-year-old Mayisela included a herd of cattle and hard cash. According to reports, King Misuzulu and Mayisela have known each other for many years and have two children. Watch the video above for more details on this story